{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RxYPo6GkFL439H8KvwsFHx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup clearly:\n\n1. The Elasticsearch cluster is using `xpack.security.authc.realms.file.file1` for authentication with a file realm.\n2. The file realm data is mounted from the `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret.\n3. The `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret only contains `ops-user` (superuser).\n4. There's a separate `user-provided-file-realm` secret that contains `report-user` (read role).\n\nThe problem is that:\n- The StatefulSet only mounts `es-file-realm-aggregate` for the file realm\n- `user-provided-file-realm` with `report-user` isn't being mounted, so `report-user` can't authenticate\n- I need to merge both secrets together so all users are available in the mounted file realm\n\nLet me check what's currently in each secret.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1783,"cache_read_input_tokens":33191,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1783},"output_tokens":39,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dfe50dc4-570e-45ad-b01e-1f2aec3e8d04","uuid":"3b1ec535-aab7-41b3-b1a3-a22b63d51bc3","request_id":"req_011CcLDbqvxFoTWxpaFxPgSz"}
