{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01H7yY5WvdUHhRZ7pQs4zMVH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Confirmed. Now I need to merge `report-user` credentials into `es-file-realm-aggregate`. \n\nThe merged `users` file will have both users:\n```\nops-user:$2a$10$JvNnOGqJ.4fWLvoeZlzkWOD/WkSnw2qCl//DigjuQWgKERgWCJLZu\nreport-user:$2a$10$IH7z2UlbU5vVpL7Fmiek9.u3v4EMR9RbS0vRIW3zhewuSmhhmXfRq\n```\n\nThe merged `users_roles` will have both role assignments. Now I'm realizing a potential issue: since the StatefulSet uses `subPath` to mount these files, the mounted volume won't automatically refresh when the secret changes. I could delete and recreate the pods, which is risky but the stateful pods should recover. Alternatively, Elasticsearch 7.x has a `reload_secure_settings` API I could use instead.\n\nActually, I'm reconsidering the approach. When mounting secrets as volumes without `subPath`, Kubernetes updates them automatically, but with `subPath` the files stay static. The current StatefulSet configuration uses `subPath` for the users, users_roles, and roles.yml files, so updating the secret alone won't propagate those changes to the running pods—I'd need to restart them. But maybe there's another way to handle this.\n\nI could either merge the changes into the aggregate secret and trigger a rolling restart of the StatefulSet, which should maintain cluster health, or I could use `kubectl exec` to write directly to the config files in each pod since Elasticsearch automatically reloads the file realm periodically.\n\nBut the config files are mounted as read-only, so I can't modify them directly in the pods. That means I have to go with the first approach: update the secret and restart the pods one at a time to keep the cluster stable.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":794,"cache_read_input_tokens":38971,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":794},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dfe50dc4-570e-45ad-b01e-1f2aec3e8d04","uuid":"95abb244-0f48-4107-8251-fd9748e7204e","request_id":"req_011CcLDfWF8twgCrMSoziNum"}
