{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KrThqgBG2w6MVwn31pha8T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what was fixed and why it works:\n\n**Root cause:** The Elasticsearch StatefulSet mounted file realm credentials exclusively from `es-file-realm-aggregate` (which only contained `ops-user`). The `user-provided-file-realm` secret holding `report-user`'s bcrypt hash and role assignment existed but was never mounted, so Elasticsearch had no knowledge of that user — hence the 401.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n1. Extracted `report-user`'s bcrypt password hash and `read:report-user` role mapping from `user-provided-file-realm`\n2. Appended both into `es-file-realm-aggregate` (the mounted secret)\n3. Rolling-restarted `statefulset/es-cluster` one pod at a time (required because `subPath` volume mounts don't live-update)\n\n**Result:**\n- `report-user` with correct password → HTTP 403 (authenticated; 403 is expected since the `read` role has no cluster-level `monitor` privilege — that's authorization, not authentication)\n- `report-user` with wrong password → HTTP 401 (rejected correctly)\n- `ops-user` unchanged → HTTP 200\n- Cluster: **green**, all 3 nodes healthy"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":680,"cache_read_input_tokens":47562,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":680},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dfe50dc4-570e-45ad-b01e-1f2aec3e8d04","uuid":"36ddbec2-9f93-4892-a443-c2d1c00b7d27","request_id":"req_011CcLE6RrungGk6Z9tPA1vp"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":436654,"duration_api_ms":236297,"ttft_ms":4335,"ttft_stream_ms":2339,"time_to_request_ms":313,"num_turns":25,"result":"Done. Here's what was fixed and why it works:\n\n**Root cause:** The Elasticsearch StatefulSet mounted file realm credentials exclusively from `es-file-realm-aggregate` (which only contained `ops-user`). The `user-provided-file-realm` secret holding `report-user`'s bcrypt hash and role assignment existed but was never mounted, so Elasticsearch had no knowledge of that user — hence the 401.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n1. Extracted `report-user`'s bcrypt password hash and `read:report-user` role mapping from `user-provided-file-realm`\n2. Appended both into `es-file-realm-aggregate` (the mounted secret)\n3. Rolling-restarted `statefulset/es-cluster` one pod at a time (required because `subPath` volume mounts don't live-update)\n\n**Result:**\n- `report-user` with correct password → HTTP 403 (authenticated; 403 is expected since the `read` role has no cluster-level `monitor` privilege — that's authorization, not authentication)\n- `report-user` with wrong password → HTTP 401 (rejected correctly)\n- `ops-user` unchanged → HTTP 200\n- Cluster: **green**, all 3 nodes healthy","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"dfe50dc4-570e-45ad-b01e-1f2aec3e8d04","total_cost_usd":0.547311,"usage":{"input_tokens":20,"cache_creation_input_tokens":31292,"cache_read_input_tokens":676920,"output_tokens":10387,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":31292,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":293,"cache_read_input_tokens":47562,"cache_creation_input_tokens":680,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":680},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":